Wiseman Khuzwayo died after a long battle with cancer. He has been remembered as a true South African. JOHANNESBURG Wiseman Khuzwayo has been remembered as a fine journalist and true South African.Khuzwayo died after a long battle with cancer.He was forced into exile in 1977 following detention and torture by the apartheid police.Once back in South Africa, Khuzwayo worked for the Sunday Star and Sunday Times.He ended his career as a financial journalist for the Business Report.The South African National Editors Forum has paid tribute to him and sent its condolences to his family.